By Raji Rasak Badagry – The police on Wednesday arraigned a 60-year-old man, Martins Anyakoro on in a Badagry Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State for allegedly posing as a Naval officer. Anyakoro os charged with two counts of impersonation and breach of peace. The Prosecution Counsel, ASP Clement Okuoimose, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on June 13 at 6:30 p.m, at the Navy Base FOB Badagry, Lagos. Okuoimose alleged that the defendant paraded himself as Navy Captain at the base. He said that the defendant also conducted himself in a manner likely to cause breach of peace by entering the Navy base and harassed officers on duty. The offenc, he said, contravened the provisions of sections 77 and 166 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Magistrate, Mr Aka Bashorun, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N200, 000 with two sureties in like sum. He adjourned the case until July 10.